First of all, it's hard to swallow this post given the past.  Sotae, I've enjoyed chatting with you frequently in game.  I think you've got it together.<br>
<br>
That said, SF's officers have complained that the calendar here is unreliable because anyone can post on it.  They went ahead and ran Naggy despite our post.  Granted, there were no conventions established yet, but given that the calendar was on a message board run by an SF member, it's a bit disheartening. <br>
<br>
I also disagree with you dragon scheduling.  For dragons that are truly random spawns (Faydedar comes to mind), first see, first kill works fine for me.  PO may or may not do the old world dragons again, but given that they spawn in a set location on a set schedule and are spawned irregularly, I don't agree to first come first serve.  Whether we use a calendar system or a rotation system is irrelevant, but some kind of system needs to be worked out.  The same is true of VS.  Not every guild can assemble enough forces the minute the servers come up to take down those spawns.  <br>
<br>
At the moment, most of the other mobs you mentioned are only w/in reach of IV, SF, and maybe PO and Slivers for now, I suspect.  Hell, most aren't even w/in reach for IV.  (Yelinak and Dain Frostweaver... that's gonna take some time.  And have you heard about the upraded gods yet... heh).  Until such time as more than one guild can handle a spawn, I don't think it's a big issue.<br>
<br>
As far as the once per week thing:  Again, there are maybe 6 guilds that are planar ready.  (The Endless is one that you didn't mention, they're planning to go to Hate on Friday).  At this point, once per week means the planes will go unscheduled for certain days.  What's the rule then, ffa?  I would suggest, instead, a rule that no guild could schedule a given plane for a friday/saturday/sunday more than 2 times per month, and no guild could schedule a given plane more than once per Monday-Thursday.  Days that are not reserved are then FFA.<br>
<br>
Lastly, before we enter into any kind or agreement, I want to know if you have the power to commit your guild to it or if you are just making a suggestion?  In otherwords, is this a case of Sotae posting his opinion or Sotae presenting the position of SF?</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>3</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:31:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: calender business</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First, let me say that I'm absolutely not speaking on behalf of IV.  I don't want to get people paranoid about IV's intentions.  I'm just stating my opinions here, heh.<br>
<br>
Something to remember about Calendar systems is that Verant will not support/enforce Calendars.<br>
<br>
