</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#212141><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucarrais.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carrais</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Administrator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>30</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:11:38 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: calender business</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">That is Sotae's opinion, though a very good one. Planes and other raid style zones that can only support one guild at a time should be reservable. Each guild should only have one event scheduled at a time, to prevent abuse. Do your event then post your next after you complete it.</font><P><IMG SRC=http://www.ece.utexas.edu/~jrichard/carrais-sig2.jpg><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neferati>Neferati</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>5</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:38:26 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http:\\207.252.219.170\neferati.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: calender business</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I understand there are many GOOD reasons to have a calendar system, but I have always disliked the idea.  Here's why...<br>
<br>
1) When a plane is reserved, it is almost always used less than half of the time.  In some instances it is rare for the entire zone is not cleared (i.e. Hate) and is usually only cleared one time.  This means when a respawn is 10 or 12 hours (and a guild clears it only once) then half of the day the zone is completely unused because it is &quot;reserved&quot;.<br>
<br>
2) Calendars get abused.<br>
<br>
3) When calendars get abused, people get less access to the planes.  Animosity builds between different guilds, leading to hatred for no real reason.<br>
<br>
I would propose instead of a calendar system, how about each raid location has a common &quot;Jump Off&quot; point.  For Hate this would be South Ro.  Fear / PoG / PoM have very obvious starting zones.  Sky isnt an issue (even though it is my favorite plane) because it is rarely utilized to it's potential.<br>
<br>
A person could &quot;camp&quot; a plane by being at the &quot;jump off point&quot;.  He would then have 3 hours to start the raid (or some other realistic time).  If the raid doesnt begin within a specific amount of time he forfeits the camp.<br>
<br>
I would like to avoid the scenario where a certain group of people camps a plane most of the time because they are &quot;creative&quot; with who schedules a planes raid on a given day. (The Nameless comes immediately to mind).<br>
<br>
I also would prefer to avoid the scenario where a plane is unused 80 percent of the time because it is scheduled, yet no one is there.  (How many times did you want to do a planes raid, and couldnt because it was &quot;reserved&quot; -- yet the people who scheduled it didnt actually do the plane on that day?)<br>
